reactor.core.dispatch.forkjoin

Class ForkJoinPool

  • java.lang.Object
    • reactor.core.dispatch.forkjoin.ForkJoinPool

  • public class ForkJoinPool
extends Object
    Simple Executor backed fork/join pool that will coalesce results from asynchronous tasks and publish them into a Promise or a Stream depending on whether you intend to fork() an execution or join() them together. tasks
    Author:
    Jon Brisbin, Stephane Maldini

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Concrete Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      <V> ForkJoinTask<V,Broadcaster<V>> fork()
      Asynchronously execute tasks added to the returned ForkJoinTask and publish the non-null results, one per task, to the Stream returned from ForkJoinTask.compose().
      <V> ForkJoinTask<ImmutableList<V>,Broadcaster<ImmutableList<V>>> join(Collection<Function<?,V>> tasks)
      Asynchronously submit the given tasks, one submit per task, to the configured Executor and collecting the results in a List that will be the fulfillment of the Promise returned from ForkJoinTask.compose().
